---
// File-style route -> under `build.format: "preserve"` this emits `/privacy.html`,
// matching the legacy Jekyll permalink exactly.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="How Because Developers are Awesome handles your data."
  canonicalPath="/privacy.html"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy policy</h1>

    <ul>
      <li>We do not sell or provide our data feeds to third parties for their use.</li>
      <li>We do partner with standard data gathering entities to collect website metrics.</li>
      <li>We opt out of third party usage with those data gathering entities whenever we can.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We believe we have minimized third party usage of your browsing habits.</p>

    <h2>Our partners</h2>

    <p>
      We partner with data gathering entities to capture how you use and interact with
      our website through behavioral metrics, heatmaps, and session replay to improve
      our products/services. Website usage data is captured using first and third-party
      cookies and other tracking technologies to determine the popularity of individual
      posts and online activity. Additionally, we use this information for site optimization.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
